description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for someone with a passion for caring for patients with breast cancer, to join the oncology CNS team at the Norfolk and Norwich University Hospital (NNUH). You will work closely with the consultants and nursing teams, acting as patient advocate, to provide the best care and treatment we have to offer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have responsibility for co-ordinating treatments, managing care, triaging symptoms and side effects, and providing psychological support for patients with breast cancer, referring on to others as appropriate. As an senior oncology clinical nurse specialist you will manage your own treatment clinics and caseload. You will lead the breast oncology nurses and facilitate service improvement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To support the delivery of a high quality, safe and compassionate healthcare service, all staff are expected to act as a role model to others in all aspects of their work and consistently demonstrate NNUH’s ‘PRIDE’ values of People focused, Respect, Dedication, Integrity and Excellence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Part time:&lt;/strong&gt; 25 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview date:&lt;/strong&gt; 19th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Open for applications:&lt;/strong&gt; 26th October 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Close for applications:&lt;/strong&gt; 8th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lisa Pedro - Oncology Clinical Nurse Specialist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tel:&lt;/strong&gt; 01603 288115&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Email:&lt;/strong&gt; lisa.pedro@nnuh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
